"/><rect x="790.0" y="152" width="26" height="11" rx="2" fill="#3fbf6a"/><rect x="821.0" y="152" width="26" height="11" rx="2" fill="#3fbf6a"/><rect x="852.0" y="152" width="26" height="11" rx="2" fill="#3fbf6a"/><rect x="883.0" y="152" width="26" height="11" rx="2" fill="#3a3c44"/><text x="834.0" y="188" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" fill="#b6b4aa">New –OH H-bond donor — large affinity jump</text><rect x="660" y="292" width="348" height="118" rx="11" fill="#212329" stroke="#f0972f" stroke-width="2.5"/><text x="834.0" y="326" text-anchor="middle" font-size="16" font-weight="800" fill="#f0972f">DIHYDRO-MITRAGYNINE</text><text x="834.0" y="347" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" font-weight="700" fill="#8c8e84" letter-spacing="0.9">µ-OPIOID RECEPTOR AFFINITY</text><rect x="759.0" y="354" width="26" height="11" rx="2" fill="#f0972f"/><rect x="790.0" y="354" width="26" height="11" rx="2" fill="#f0972f"/><rect x="821.0" y="354" width="26" height="11" rx="2" fill="#3a3c44"/><rect x="852.0" y="354" width="26" height="11" rx="2" fill="#3a3c44"/><rect x="883.0" y="354" width="26" height="11" rx="2" fill="#3a3c44"/><text x="834.0" y="390" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" fill="#b6b4aa">Saturated bond adds conformational flexibility</text><rect x="1380" y="12" width="356" height="118" rx="11" fill="#212329" stroke="#e0922f" stroke-width="2.5"/><text x="1558.0" y="46" text-anchor="middle" font-size="16" font-weight="800" fill="#e0922f">7-ACETOXYMITRAGYNINE</text><text x="1558.0" y="67" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" font-weight="700" fill="#8c8e84" letter-spacing="0.9">µ-OPIOID RECEPTOR AFFINITY</text><rect x="1483.0" y="74" width="26" height="11" rx="2" fill="#e0922f"/><rect x="1514.0" y="74" width="26" height="11" rx="2" fill="#e0922f"/><rect x="1545.0" y="74" width="26" height="11" rx="2" fill="#e0922f"/><rect x="1576.0" y="74" width="26" height="11" rx="2" fill="#3a3c44"/><rect x="1607.0" y="74" width="26" height="11" rx="2" fill="#3a3c44"/><text x="1558.0" y="110" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" fill="#b6b4aa">Ester caps the 7-OH; hydrolyzes back to 7-OH</text><rect x="1380" y="152" width="356" height="118" rx="11" fill="#212329" stroke="#a78bfa" stroke-width="2.5"/><text x="1558.0" y="180" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12.5" font-weight="800" fill="#a78bfa">DIHYDRO-7-HYDROXYMITRAGYNINE</text><text x="1558.0" y="196" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" font-style="italic" font-weight="700" fill="#a6a499">aka MGM-15</text><text x="1558.0" y="213" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" font-weight="700" fill="#8c8e84" letter-spacing="0.9">µ-OPIOID RECEPTOR AFFINITY</text><rect x="1483.0" y="220" width="26" height="11" rx="2" fill="#a78bfa"/><rect x="1514.0" y="220" width="26" height="11" rx="2" fill="#a78bfa"/><rect x="1545.0" y="220" width="26" height="11" rx="2" fill="#a78bfa"/><rect x="1576.0" y="220" width="26" height="11" rx="2" fill="#a78bfa"/><rect x="1607.0" y="220" width="26" height="11" rx="2" fill="#a78bfa"/><text x="1558.0" y="253" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" fill="#b6b4aa">Flexible indoline — tightest receptor fit</text><rect x="1380" y="292" width="356" height="118" rx="11" fill="#212329" stroke="#f0506e" stroke-width="2.5"/><text x="1558.0" y="326" text-anchor="middle" font-size="16" font-weight="800" fill="#f0506e">PSEUDOINDOXYL</text><text x="1558.0" y="347" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" font-weight="700" fill="#8c8e84" letter-spacing="0.9">µ-OPIOID RECEPTOR AFFINITY</text><rect x="1483.0" y="354" width="26" height="11" rx="2" fill="#f0506e"/><rect x="1514.0" y="354" width="26" height="11" rx="2" fill="#f0506e"/><rect x="1545.0" y="354" width="26" height="11" rx="2" fill="#f0506e"/><rect x="1576.0" y="354" width="26" height="11" rx="2" fill="#f0506e"/><rect x="1607.0" y="354" width="26" height="11" rx="2" fill="#3a3c44"/><text x="1558.0" y="390" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" fill="#b6b4aa">Carbonyl H-bond acceptor; planar indoxyl core</text></svg></div>
    <p class="map-cap">Every kratom alkaloid in this chart is a structural modification of <b>mitragynine</b>. Bars show approximate <b>relative</b> &micro;-opioid receptor affinity (not absolute K&#x1d62;). <span class="rdot">Reduction steps (&plus; H&#x2082;, purple)</span> consistently raise affinity &mdash; saturating a double bond adds conformational flexibility for a tighter receptor fit. Morphine is not shown: it is a phenanthrene-class opioid, <b>not</b> a structural derivative of mitragynine.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="panel-trend">
    <div class="ptitle">General trend in &micro;-opioid receptor binding &mdash; affinity / potency</div>
    <div class="pbody">
      <div class="trend-scale"><span>&larr; Lower affinity / potency</span><span>Higher affinity / potency &rarr;</span></div>
      <div class="trend"><div class="titem" style="--c:#26b8a4">
      <div class="tname">Mitragynine</div>
      <div class="tlevel">low–moderate</div>
      <div class="tki">Kᵢ ≈ 80–200 nM</div>
    </div><div class="tarrow">&rsaquo;</div><div class="titem" style="--c:#f0972f">
      <div class="tname">Dihydro-mitragynine (DHM)</div>
      <div class="tlevel">moderate</div>
      <div class="tki">Kᵢ ≈ 10–30 nM</div>
    </div><div class="tarrow">&rsaquo;</div><div class="titem" style="--c:#f0506e">
      <div class="tname">Pseudoindoxyl mitragynine</div>
      <div class="tlevel">moderate–high</div>
      <div class="tki">Kᵢ ≈ 0.2–1 nM</div>
    </div><div class="tarrow">&rsaquo;</div><div class="titem" style="--c:#5b86ff">
      <div class="tname">Morphine</div>
      <div class="tlevel">high; reference</div>
      <div class="tki">Kᵢ ≈ 1.0 nM</div>
    </div><div class="tarrow">&rsaquo;</div><div class="titem" style="--c:#e0922f">
      <div class="tname">7-Acetoxymitragynine</div>
      <div class="tlevel">moderate–high</div>
      <div class="tki">Kᵢ not established</div>
    </div><div class="tarrow">&rsaquo;</div><div class="titem" style="--c:#3fbf6a">
      <div class="tname">7-Hydroxymitragynine</div>
      <div class="tlevel">very high</div>
      <div class="tki">Kᵢ ≈ 0.2–0.6 nM</div>
    </div><div class="tarrow">&rsaquo;</div><div class="titem" style="--c:#a78bfa">
      <div class="tname">Dihydro-7-hydroxymitragynine (MGM-15)</div>
      <div class="tlevel">very high</div>
      <div class="tki">Kᵢ ≈ 0.03–0.2 nM</div>
    </div></div>
      <p class="trend-foot">Potency rankings vary by species and by the outcome measured (receptor binding, analgesia, behavioral models, etc.).</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  
